metadata.description: Ships come in many shapes & sizes. Interceptor-class vessels are designed as hunter-killers, far outmaneuvering larger craft.

metadata.description: For those unwilling to believe in karma, many ways to get ahead can be found.

metadata.description: To Leonid, the Great One bestowed his ability to control & corrupt the minds of others. Entire forces have been lost to his poison-laced words, only to show up fighting under his banner the next day.

metadata.description: All are welcome aboard Sanctuary. Ruled with an iron fist by the Echelon Cartel, it serves as a safe haven for the misfits of the system.

metadata.name: Kingpin's Tithe [SE]
metadata.description: All men, kings and pauper alike, pay the Kingpin’s Tithe, the tales of what happens when it is denied a constant reminder.

metadata.name: Shoshanna's Standard [SE]
metadata.description: Whenever they saw her flag making its way through the ranks they instinctively surged forward. They knew there was almost no injury she could not mend.

metadata.name: Progenitor Pod [SE]
metadata.description: Aetio leaned forward, and peered into the dense cellular reanimating fluid and pulled out an arm that immediately fell apart. She frowned. “This one needs more time.”

metadata.name: Drusian Exhorator [SE]
metadata.description: “The blood of Drusius Alpha flows through us all, his teachings burned into our memories. Embrace the power he has bestowed upon us!” - Vania Beta, Drusian Exhorator

metadata.name: Freydis, Echelon Kingpin [SE]
metadata.description: Lowlifes and Generals alike have found themselves in Freydis' halls aboard the space station Sanctuary, asking for her aid. She offers it freely, safe in the knowledge that every debt will be repaid.

metadata.name: Tane, Shield of Meev'Tsar
metadata.description: Meev'Tsar was carved from the mountain's stone. What could Tane carve from you?

metadata.name: Cost of Creation [SE]
metadata.description: The fools say we have lost our humanity, they never knew it was a resource to be bargained with.

metadata.name: Mortal Echo [SE]
metadata.description: We do not corrupt. We simply act upon what is inside.

metadata.name: Artillery Volley
metadata.description: We fired from the safety of the walls and watched the garish brutes flee. They underestimated Marcolian artillery.

metadata.name: Gambler's Coin [SE]
metadata.description: “Never give me the odds.” - Sammy “Four Fingers” Roth

metadata.name: Scimitar Scout Bike [SE]
metadata.description: Agile and durable enough to traverse the roughest terrain, the Scimitar Bike serves as a vital tool of the Marcolian Scout Corps. You never forget a full speed flyby, if you're lucky enough to even see it.

metadata.name: Maritus, Aetian Recombinant [SE]
metadata.description: “My child you are truly unique. A living, breathing, archivist lab. I tell this to all the blanks, but you above all others truly can be anything you wish.” - Hadriana Beta, 1st Archivist

metadata.name: Gambler's Coin [PL]
metadata.description: “Never give me the odds.” - Sammy “Four Fingers” Roth

metadata.name: Mournful Delta [SE]
metadata.description: Julius Delta looked down into eyes identical to his own, kissed his hand and bid himself farewell.

metadata.name: Flurry of Genius [SE]
metadata.description: Never underestimate the Augencore’s resilience. You may think you dealt them a crushing defeat, to them, it was in fact a vital lesson.

metadata.name: Cape of Char Mahal
metadata.description: “This? It belonged to my father. When I was young, he used to tell me defense can win almost any fight, and when it can’t, at least I have my cape.” - Nehemiah

metadata.name: Upcycled Technology [SE]
metadata.description: Nothing wasted, a second chance for everything.

metadata.name: Manipulation Ray [SE]
metadata.description: Originally developed with medical applications in mind, the combat medics of the Marcolian forces quickly found a more direct use for the technology.

metadata.name: Earthbreaker Cannon [SE]
metadata.description: The ultimate expression of Marcolian firepower. Capable of interplanetary bombardment, Earthbreaker Cannons often win a battle without ever having to fire, such is their fearsome reputation. Troopers report never getting the hum of its particle accelerator ring out of their ears.

metadata.name: Neutron Bomb [SE]
metadata.description: When negotiation fails, the Marcolian simply wipe the slate clean, and build in their image.

metadata.name: Singularity Portal [PL]
metadata.description: A tear in space, materialising just as swiftly as it vanishes.

metadata.name: Lord Harf, Cartel Treasurer
metadata.description: No one is exactly sure why he calls himself a Lord, but so far, none have dared to ask.

metadata.name: Ashes to Ashes [SE]
metadata.description: What we become, is what we came from.

metadata.name: The Great Enigma [SE]
metadata.description: It is near impossible to fight that which you can not see. It is impossible to fight that which you can not hope to comprehend.

metadata.name: Freydis, Echelon Kingpin
metadata.description: Lowlifes and Generals alike have found themselves in Freydis' halls aboard the space station Sanctuary, asking for her aid. She offers it freely, safe in the knowledge that every debt will be repaid.

metadata.name: Trade Secrets [SE]
metadata.description: More valuable than Trilithium, more guarded than the High Command of Mars. The Augencore's secrets are their most prized possession.

metadata.name: Akara, Rebel General [SE]
metadata.description: “6 years I grovelled in the Marcolian Academies, and for what? I quit and became a god. I spit on my former so called comrades.”

metadata.name: Grove Altruist
metadata.description: The Grove teaches us that life and death are one and the same, each one a path to the other.

metadata.name: Hallowed Burial Ground [SE]
metadata.description: Most Earthen do not fear death, for they know that even in their fall, they will sow the seeds of future life.

metadata.name: Gallian Recombinant [SE]
metadata.description: “Maritus may be one of a kind, but if she is the future of the Children of Europa. We must remake ourselves in her image just as we are made in Galli’s.” - Fourth Palm of Galli

metadata.name: Gambler's Coin [SE]
metadata.description: “Never give me the odds.” - Sammy “Four Fingers” Roth

metadata.name: Parallel Masterpiece // Alpha // Revitalizing Growth
metadata.description: Parallel Masterpieces - Alpha Set - Earthen: Revitalizing Growth // Art by Oscar Mar // 2021

metadata.name: Wannabe Warlord [SE]
metadata.description: This guy took the phrase “Dream Big” very, very seriously.

metadata.name: Lord Harf, Cartel Treasurer [SE]
metadata.description: No one is exactly sure why he calls himself a Lord, but so far, none have dared to ask.

metadata.name: Solar Grenade [SE]
metadata.description: “The heat kicked out by one of these things is enough to melt the armour on a Lancer Tank, so with that in mind, here is how you put the safety on.” - Marcolian Instructor

metadata.name: Trade Route Ambush [SE]
metadata.description: Most trading vessel captains learn the importance of hiring an escort sooner rather than later.

metadata.name: Machine-Learning Matrix [SE]
metadata.description: The spark of genius comes from the Augencore themselves, but the relentless optimization falls onto their ever-learning central computers.

metadata.name: Gaia's Call
metadata.description: If you think we Earthen fervently defend this planet, just wait until you push her too far.

metadata.name: Mizra Loyalist [SE]
metadata.description: The beauty of Mizrakadesh has earned its tenants' adoration - and concern.

metadata.name: Shepherd of the Fallen [SE]
metadata.description: The Great One gave us life. It is only right that in time we give it back.

metadata.name: Spider Drone
metadata.description: The Shroud’s machinations begin long before they ever arrive. A single drone sent through the void, capable of sabotage & assassinations, the Spider leaves a colony in disarray before the attack.

metadata.name: Warden
metadata.description: They said it could not be done, but fitting a cannon to the simplest tool creates a deadly weapon.

metadata.name: Power Instructor
metadata.description: He does not bestow gifts, but teaches others to recognise their own.

metadata.name: Infused Shaman
metadata.description: So skilled in the ways healing, the shaman can bring people back from the brink of death. But the cost… the earth demands balance.

metadata.name: Shady Merchant
metadata.description: No returns, no questions, no demonstrations. You break it, you buy it, if you survive.

metadata.name: Sacred Siphoner
metadata.description: The most talented among us can beseech the void for resources, and barely even lose themselves in the process.

metadata.name: Innovative Apprentice
metadata.description: Ever learning, ever adapting. The future generations of the Augencore know they will be the ones to lead the way.

metadata.name: Formidable Presence
metadata.description: The Earthen are a peace loving kind. Meev’Tsar is the exception that proves the rule.

metadata.name: Virulent Spores
metadata.description: Deadly to the touch, let alone if inhaled. The Earthen learn to use all their resources in defense of their land.

metadata.name: Reliant Gamma
metadata.description: Kathari are the tide. They flow as one. Together, there is no single barrier that can stop them.

metadata.name: Valerusi Standard Bearer
metadata.description: “My friends, it is a fine day to die.” - Aramus Beta, Standard Bearer for the 8th Valerusi Cohort

metadata.name: The Staff of Shoshanna
metadata.description: I heard that what she can do goes beyond healing. She not only mends broken bones and knits flesh, but she can give you power you never even knew you had.

metadata.name: Aurora Fungi
metadata.description: Easy to find for a skilled gatherer, but harvesting is an exceptionally delicate process. Valuable for its natural properties and a delight for the more adventurous during festivals.

metadata.name: Graphene Batteries
metadata.description: They are more of a slow release explosion than a battery. Comprised of highly volatile chemicals, it has a singular cycle life and outputs immense amounts of energy. Handle with fear lest we all feel the catastrophic consequences.

metadata.name: The Tree of Nehemiah
metadata.description: They say its bark is so hard as to be nearly indestructible. It has stood here for thousands of years and will continue to for thousands more. Let it be a beacon for all those who stand for earth.

metadata.name: Revitalizing Growth
metadata.description: The breath of life flows through the Earthen, giving them strength to stand once again and defend their home.

metadata.name: Rug Poll
metadata.description: Ah, rug pollen. Grass near the source turns to a soft, plush velvet. Feels great between the toes, but get too comfortable and you’ll be too dizzy to tell the difference between your lover and a big ol’ blacktusk. Nasty little trick.

metadata.name: Recon
metadata.description: Even the smallest blade can be deadly if you know where and how to strike.

metadata.name: Sower of Unrest
metadata.description: Gaffar’s teachings were rarely contentious, though not entirely devoid of detractors. But not all ears were receptive.

metadata.name: Primea Conduit
metadata.description: The power to protect ones friends is amongst the highest honors of the Earthen. It is rarely wasted.

metadata.name: Life Well
metadata.description: Not all that awaits explorers of deep space is horrifying. Much of what is waiting to be discovered is, in human terms, quite miraculous. Tonight we bathe in the cosmos itself.

metadata.name: Repurposed Hardware
metadata.description: Those first years on Mars would have been the death of us, but our ingenuity and resourcefulness kept us alive. Now it will be our enemies' downfall.

metadata.name: Unfair Advantage
metadata.description: Taking on an Augencore warrior means taking on the genius of the whole ship.

metadata.name: EMP Shockwave
metadata.description: EMP Shockwave

metadata.name: Ruthless Sergeant
metadata.description: Courage falters. She does not.

metadata.name: Erasure [PL]
metadata.description: A corpse can become a martyr. So we shall turn you to nothing.

metadata.name: The Flat Circle [PL]
metadata.description: In time, you will learn the meaning of eternity.

metadata.name: Hired Gun [PL]
metadata.description: Another of the Black Market’s specialties, you’ll find few questions are asked as long as your payment is on time.

metadata.name: Chem-Crazed Bruiser [PL]
metadata.description: A veritable cocktail of combat enhancing substances, straight into the bloodstream. Useful in tight situations, not so much in diplomacy.

metadata.name: Combat Veteran [SE]
metadata.description: In the ways of war are best learned on the job, and there is no greater teacher than pain

metadata.name: Enduring Immunus [SE]
metadata.description: Feeling death’s slow and icy embrace, Vitus Delta makes a stand.

metadata.name: Inspiring Teacher [SE]
metadata.description: She inspired those she taught. They were not going to let her death go unavenged.

metadata.name: Formatician's Exalt [SE]
metadata.description: Each Hydroleum has an Exalt. They are the bridge by which the Kathari travel from death to rebirth.

metadata.name: Life Siphon [SE]
metadata.description: “The group of suspected Shroud we encountered bore no arms, and moved with no urgency. Yet, many of us were lost that day.” - Unknown Kathari Archaeologist

metadata.name: Wisened Elder [SE]
metadata.description: Not all of us are here to fight, but we can all find a way to help

metadata.name: Technophobic Warrior [SE]
metadata.description: His ancestors hated people looking at their phones all the time.

metadata.name: Unstable Shield Generator [SE]
metadata.description: “Uhh, Captain? I’m not sure our Shield is meant to be making that hissing noise”

metadata.name: Chem-Crazed Bruiser [SE]
metadata.description: A veritable cocktail of combat enhancing substances, straight into the bloodstream. Useful in tight situations, not so much in diplomacy.

metadata.name: Black Market Smuggler [SE]
metadata.description: Anything, anywhere. The Black Market is hard to beat for convenience.

metadata.name: Improvised Projectile [SE]
metadata.description: “Aerodynamics be damned, we can make it work” - Augencore Ship’s Gunner

metadata.name: Singularity Steward [SE]
metadata.description: Every member of the Stewards would gladly give their life to prevent anyone getting close to discovering the Singularity. Thankfully, that’s not a fight that many would be foolish enough to take.

metadata.name: Collateral Damage [SE]
metadata.description: Try as we might, there will always be unwanted casualties of war. Ideally, more for them than for us.

metadata.name: Tome of Aetio [SE]
metadata.description: “When all seems lost, remember that we are Kathari. Each of us hold the knowledge of a thousand deaths. Loss is only another path to victory.” - Aetio, Exalted Hydrolist

metadata.name: Scanner Array [SE]
metadata.description: Long before you see us, we will know you are coming.

metadata.name: TE4 Interceptor [SE]
metadata.description: Ships come in many shapes & sizes. Interceptor-class vessels are designed as hunter-killers, far outmaneuvering larger craft.

metadata.name: Tome of Aetio [SE]
metadata.description: “When all seems lost, remember that we are Kathari. Each of us hold the knowledge of a thousand deaths. Loss is only another path to victory.” - Aetio, Exalted Hydrolist

metadata.name: Alkaline Hydrolist [SE]
metadata.description: “Welcome to the Hydroleum. Don’t forget your noseplugs. The smell is atrocious, at least that’s what they tell me.” - Chrysus, Alkaline Hydrolist

metadata.name: Crimson Fleet Machinist [SE]
metadata.description: Tasked with maintaining the fearsome armored brigades of Mars while they are in transit, the machinists carry out their duty with utmost care.

metadata.name: Cape of Char Mahal [SE]
metadata.description: “This? It belonged to my father. When I was young, he used to tell me defense can win almost any fight, and when it can’t, at least I have my cape.” - Nehemiah

metadata.name: Desperate Measures [SE]
metadata.description: Desperate times have always called for these.

metadata.name: Hired Gun [SE]
metadata.description: Another of the Black Market’s specialties, you’ll find few questions are asked as long as your payment is on time.

metadata.name: Honored Steward [SE]
metadata.description: The elite of the elite, woe unto anyone who finds themselves the prey of such a being.

metadata.name: Heavy Weapons Team [SE]
metadata.description: Trained to work in perfect unison, the crewmen of the Marcolian Artillery Corps are the finest, and most lethal, gunners in the system.

metadata.name: Student of Shoshanna [SE]
metadata.description: Many among the Earthen believe studying the lessons of the past holds the key to our future.

metadata.name: Change of Heart [SE]
metadata.description: Look around and see what we are fighting over. We feel it and we can control it, and you are now a part of it. Violence and anger are a stain upon this vista. Find your calm and lower your weapon. Be at peace.

metadata.name: Sacred Destruction [SE]
metadata.description: To Bela, the Great One bestowed a mere echo of his vast ability to destroy & remake as he sees fit. Bela’s faith is matched by few, as she views her role as divine purpose, arriving to aid only those Shroud she deems worthy of witnessing a vessel of their Master.

metadata.name: Marcolian Bannerman [SE]
metadata.description: The Banner of Mars flies high amongst the Marcolian forces. The act of carrying it is a great honour, often awarded to those who have shown great courage in past conflicts, as it is to be guarded with their life.

metadata.name: Change of Heart [SE]
metadata.description: Look around and see what we are fighting over. We feel it and we can control it, and you are now a part of it. Violence and anger are a stain upon this vista. Find your calm and lower your weapon. Be at peace.

metadata.name: Steward of the Garden [SE]
metadata.description: Some beat their swords into plowshares. She preferred a trowel.

metadata.name: Erasure [SE]
metadata.description: A corpse can become a martyr. So we shall turn you to nothing.

metadata.name: Second Chance [SE]
metadata.description: Everyone deserves one.

metadata.name: Echelon Heavy [SE]
metadata.description: “Ah, I see you’ve met my business associate, Mr. Knuckles. Don’t worry about him, he will be a silent partner unless there’s any reason for him to become involved…”

metadata.name: Scrapheap Salvager [SE]
metadata.description: It’s not a glamorous job, but it serves a vital purpose ensuring little goes to waste.

metadata.name: Hydrolist Chamber [SE]
metadata.description: “I will see you again, my friend. Maybe even later today.” - Jubia Maximus Delta

metadata.name: Collateral Damage [SE]
metadata.description: Try as we might, there will always be unwanted casualties of war. Ideally, more for them than for us.

metadata.name: Beloved Donor [SE]
metadata.description: “The greatest honour is to bestow oneself unto others.” - Octavia Delta, 2nd Cohort Physic

metadata.name: Antius's Forecast [SE]
metadata.description: Antius was amongst the best of us. Perhaps, with this opportunity, you shall be too.

metadata.name: Mercenary Gunslinger [SE]
metadata.description: If you’ve got the money, I’ve got the aim.

metadata.name: Cunning Scipian [SE]
metadata.description: “Scipians, we were grown for this. Our bodies will fuel the engines of war.” - Scipius Magnus Alpha

metadata.name: Synchronicity [SE]
metadata.description: I can always feel my brothers and sisters. Their thoughts are mine. Their feelings are mine. Their intent is mine. We may be many, but we act as one.

metadata.name: Scanner Array [SE]
metadata.description: Long before you see us, we will know you are coming.

metadata.name: Fire Support Base [SE]
metadata.description: Marcolians fiercely defend the territory they have gained, unwilling to give even an inch.

metadata.name: Mind Twister [SE]
metadata.description: The Shroud cloud the minds of their enemies, making it near impossible to tell friend from foe.

metadata.name: Doctor's Assistant [SE]
metadata.description: Sometimes healing requires many hands.

metadata.name: Grove Altruist [SE]
metadata.description: The Grove teaches us that life and death are one and the same, each one a path to the other.

metadata.name: Unseen Allies [SE]
metadata.description: “You may think you have me cornered, Kathari dogs, but I assure you the numbers are on my side”

metadata.name: Beacon of Gnaeus [SE]
metadata.description: The inspiring tales of Gnaeus Valerus Alpha’s valiant deeds spread far and wide. The mere mention of his name sowing fear in the enemies of the Kathari, and inspiring great feats of strength from his army.

metadata.name: Backup Copy [SE]
metadata.description: Before any of you dream of rebellion, know that you are one of thousands. With a mere push of a button, you can and will be replaced.

metadata.name: Smuggled Supplies [SE]
metadata.description: It never hurts to be prepared, and sometimes, it pays dividends.

metadata.name: Dark Dealings [SE]
metadata.description: A deal with the devil? Oh no, this is something far greater.

metadata.name: Demolecularize [SE]
metadata.description: The Shroud often leave behind no trace of their victims, no evidence, no clue as to their goals. Entire ships, gone in the blink of an eye.

metadata.name: Ocular Implant [SE]
metadata.description: Never play an Augencore Warrior in a game of Poker.

metadata.name: Engine Whisperer [SE]
metadata.description: The engines of the New Dawn barely resemble those the ship launched with centuries ago. Legends say the New Dawn can appear at almost any place in the system instantaneously, though few escape to tell the tale.

metadata.name: Longbow Personnel Carrier [SE]
metadata.description: Named after an ancient weapon of war, the Longbow delivers it’s lethal payload straight to the heart of the enemy.

metadata.name: Automation Expert [SE]
metadata.description: Automation is a highly controversial subject among the Augencore. Many employ its clear benefits, but there are those who claim nothing can replace the human touch in operating their machines.

metadata.name: Archivist's Pride [SE]
metadata.description: Our sequences are retained and so too, we hope, our souls.

metadata.name: Cutting Edge [SE]
metadata.description: For times when the simplest solution suffices.

metadata.name: Life Stream [SE]
metadata.description: The prophecy told them to follow the stream, for it would lead to life eternal.

metadata.name: Vengeful Ally [SE]
metadata.description: Love is not the most powerful force in the world. Spite is.

metadata.name: Fanatical Crewman [SE]
metadata.description: Many aboard the New Dawn seek to appease their unseen masters in the hopes of gaining power akin to the champions of the Shroud. Few are deemed worthy.

metadata.name: Paradigm Shift [SE]
metadata.description: We are Earthen. We are those that remained and as a reward the Earth itself can protect us. You just need to ask.

metadata.name: Reluctant Berserker
metadata.description: Every life is precious and yet they are willing to take without regard. Well, if it’s death they want then I will show it to them.

metadata.name: Pocket Dimension
metadata.description: It sure beats a traditional bag of tricks.

metadata.name: Machine-Learning Matrix
metadata.description: The spark of genius comes from the Augencore themselves, but the relentless optimization falls onto their ever-learning central computers.

metadata.name: Scimitar Scout Bike
metadata.description: Agile and durable enough to traverse the roughest terrain, the Scimitar Bike serves as a vital tool of the Marcolian Scout Corps. You never forget a full speed flyby, if you're lucky enough to even see it.

metadata.name: Cleanse the Earth
metadata.description: We humans can sometimes forget the damage we do to the earth and that the only way to fix it is to wipe the slate clean. Looks like its time for a reminder.

metadata.name: Commandeered Warship
metadata.description: The Penshaw is an 18 gun battlecruiser intended to fly with a full complement of 190 souls. For Captain K’ra and his crew of six, this was going to be quite the challenge.

metadata.name: Sixth Palm of Galli
metadata.description: “Kathari exemplify change. We must embrace change, if we are to grow as a people. Death is simply another change.” - Sixth teaching of Galli

metadata.name: Star Chart
metadata.description: The map was lying, then. The map never lies!

metadata.name: Arrisah Skyscout
metadata.description: Mawaan's lessons still keep safe the city in the clouds.

metadata.name: Shepherd of the Fallen
metadata.description: The Great One gave us life. It is only right that in time we give it back.

metadata.name: Anti-Organic Pulse
metadata.description: Most Augencore are loath to employ such devastating measures. For Arak, everything is a means to an end.

metadata.name: Iron Corps Rifleman
metadata.description: Mars expects that every man and woman will do their duty. Many of those look to the Iron Corps for inspiration.

metadata.name: Drusian Exhorator
metadata.description: “The blood of Drusius Alpha flows through us all, his teachings burned into our memories. Embrace the power he has bestowed upon us!” - Vania Beta, Drusian Exhorator

metadata.name: Grove Guardian
metadata.description: Of all Earths locations, perhaps none are defended as fiercely as the holy groves.

metadata.name: Eye of Galli
metadata.description: Barely a speck among the stars, the Eye of Galli looks down upon the battlefield. Jumping excitedly out of his seat, the Second Palm of Galli points at the battle map. “That one! I want that one, Gamma! Fire the beam.”

metadata.name: Upcycled Technology
metadata.description: Nothing wasted, a second chance for everything.

metadata.name: Wannabe Warlord
metadata.description: This guy took the phrase “Dream Big” very, very seriously.

metadata.name: Singularity Portal
metadata.description: A tear in space, materialising just as swiftly as it vanishes.

metadata.name: H.A.D.E.S. War Mech
metadata.description: The Heavy Assault Designated Exoskeleton System, piloted by augmented & expertly trained pilots, the H.A.D.E.S. stands as a steadfast symbol of the Augencore’s might. The armament of each mech varies, as pilots customize theirs heavily from the stock loadout.

metadata.name: Cost of Creation
metadata.description: The fools say we have lost our humanity, they never knew it was a resource to be bargained with.

metadata.name: Infused Core
metadata.description: “This thing will make light speed travel seem like a joke! Just uh, don’t drop it ok?” - Black Market Vendor

metadata.name: Dauntless Axeman
metadata.description: Strike me down, for you would do little but return me to my Mother’s embrace.

metadata.name: Ammo Hauler
metadata.description: Any true general knows that wars are won and lost as much on logistics as the bravery of the men and women fighting.

metadata.name: Mournful Delta
metadata.description: Julius Delta looked down into eyes identical to his own, kissed his hand and bid himself farewell.

metadata.name: Dimension Shifter
metadata.description: The Marcolian simply vanished, and in his place stood something different, something strange.

metadata.name: Reality Manipulator
metadata.description: You can raise all the arms you want against me. The gifts of my master far outweigh the trinkets of yours.

metadata.name: Cytokinesis
metadata.description: Imitation is flattery, but reproducing perfection is divine.

metadata.name: Solar Grenade
metadata.description: “The heat kicked out by one of these things is enough to melt the armour on a Lancer Tank, so with that in mind, here is how you put the safety on.” - Marcolian Instructor

metadata.name: Ship's Armory
metadata.description: “Oh the loot to be had aboard one of those foundry vessels my boys! But alas, your captain has had too much synthrum, the damn things are impossible to take.” - Captain K’ra

metadata.name: Emissary of Gaffar
metadata.description: Everyone has their limit. Eventually even the hardest soldier sees enough death to consider laying down their arms.

metadata.name: Tabula Rasa
metadata.description: “Young one, what shall we grant you? Galli’s strength and poise? Aetio’s ingenuity? Or perhaps my dashing good looks?” - Hadrius Beta, 3rd Archivist

metadata.name: Ashes to Ashes
metadata.description: What we become, is what we came from.

metadata.name: Master Poisoner
metadata.description: “Anything can be bought for a price in the black market; exquisite gems, voyages to distant worlds, untraceable lethal doses of a variety of substances…”

metadata.name: A.E.G.I.S. Generator
metadata.description: Augmented Energy Guard Individual System, the A.E.G.I.S. One of the Augencore’s most vital inventions for survival in a hostile world.

metadata.name: Amperage
metadata.description: Sometimes, there is value to be found in going beyond the recommended limits.

metadata.name: Annihilate
metadata.description: Where there once was, now, there simply is not.

metadata.name: Mizra Loyalist
metadata.description: The beauty of Mizrakadesh has earned its tenants' adoration - and concern.

metadata.name: Pocket Dimension
metadata.description: It sure beats a traditional bag of tricks.

metadata.name: Mechanize
metadata.description: We are masters of our own fate. We will advance beyond our mortal confines.

metadata.name: Reclamator
metadata.description: In Space everything is precious. There's no such thing as scrap, just parts we don't know how to use yet.

metadata.name: Manipulation Ray
metadata.description: Originally developed with medical applications in mind, the combat medics of the Marcolian forces quickly found a more direct use for the technology.

metadata.name: Seer's Stone
metadata.description: Do not discard the traditions of old, for sometimes they illuminate the path ahead.

metadata.name: The Staff of Shoshanna [PL]
metadata.description: I heard that what she can do goes beyond healing. She not only mends broken bones and knits flesh, but she can give you power you never even knew you had.

metadata.name: Pyrrhic Victory [PL]
metadata.description: When we look back on this day, I hope we can say it was worth it.

metadata.name: Crew Boss [PL]
metadata.description: “We don’t need any officers or chain of command, we know who to trust.”

metadata.name: Strength of Mars [PL]
metadata.description: Those first years on Mars would have been the death of us, but our ingenuity and resourcefulness kept us alive. Now it will be our enemies' downfall.

metadata.name: EMP Shockwave [PL]
metadata.description: Winning a battle is significantly easier once your opponent can’t fight back.

metadata.name: Beseech The Gifted [PL]
metadata.description: The Gifted are rarely impressed, but the rewards for managing such a feat can be immense.

metadata.name: Virulent Spores [PL]
metadata.description: Deadly to the touch, let alone if inhaled. The Earthen learn to use all their resources in defense of their land.

metadata.name: Innovative Apprentice [PL]
metadata.description: Ever learning, ever adapting. The future generations of the Augencore know they will be the ones to lead the way.

metadata.name: Warden
metadata.description: They said it could not be done, but fitting a cannon to the simplest tool creates a deadly weapon.

metadata.name: Enhanced Exoskeleton
metadata.description: “I swear, he lifted a Lancer Tank by himself… what? Why are you looking at me like that!” - Conversation overheard in a Marcolian trench.

metadata.name: Kamuy Protector
metadata.description: There is an ancient Earthen saying about these warriors. Roughly translated it comes out as “Don’t poke the Kamuy”

metadata.name: Polyploidian Vessel
metadata.description: “Young one, fear not the coming battle. With this vessel, you will overwhelm them entirely.” - Indutius, Master Armorer

metadata.name: Primea Conduit
metadata.description: The power to protect ones friends is amongst the highest honors of the Earthen. It is rarely wasted.

metadata.name: Shielded Assassin
metadata.description: Personal Shield Devices are extraordinarily expensive, but the lucky few who own them would agree it is a price worth paying.

metadata.name: Graphene Batteries
metadata.description: They are more of a slow release explosion than a battery. Comprised of highly volatile chemicals, it has a singular cycle life and outputs immense amounts of energy. Handle with fear lest we all feel the catastrophic consequences.

metadata.name: Reliant Gamma
metadata.description: Kathari are the tide. They flow as one. Together, there is no single barrier that can stop them.

metadata.name: Nullifier Acolyte
metadata.description: “It was like nothing I’ve felt before. Like all my senses being suffocated at once, I’m lucky Soleia was there to take him down.” - Earthen healer’s journal after first contact with a Shroud kill team.

metadata.name: Universal Soldier
metadata.description: Know your enemy. Their movements, their plans, even their thoughts - these are your weapons. Arm yourself.

metadata.name: Squad Traitor
metadata.description: For those unwilling to believe in karma, many ways to get ahead can be found.

metadata.name: Warden
metadata.description: They said it could not be done, but fitting a cannon to the simplest tool creates a deadly weapon.

metadata.name: Disciple of Maritus
metadata.description: “The Kathari are like a weed - fell one, and 3 take its place. Be careful out there, pilot.” - Jahn, Chief Engineer

metadata.name: Aurora Fungi
metadata.description: Easy to find for a skilled gatherer, but harvesting is an exceptionally delicate process. Valuable for its natural properties and a delight for the more adventurous during festivals.

metadata.name: Ardent Negotiator
metadata.description: There are times when someone needs to step in and show them that fighting isn’t always the best solution.

metadata.name: The Tree of Nehemiah
metadata.description: They say its bark is so hard as to be nearly indestructible. It has stood here for thousands of years and will continue to for thousands more. Let it be a beacon for all those who stand for earth.

metadata.name: Enthalpy's Grasp
metadata.description: Crushing. Overwhelming. Few can resist.

metadata.name: THUNDR-01 Munitions
metadata.description: Prototype THUNDR-01 Shells. Designated for field testing by Combat Overseer Arak. Extreme caution advised.

metadata.name: Spider Drone
metadata.description: The Shroud’s machinations begin long before they ever arrive. A single drone sent through the void, capable of sabotage & assassinations, the Spider leaves a colony in disarray before the attack.

metadata.name: Unnatural Selection
metadata.description: Formaticians have designed us to be the best versions of ourselves. They are the sculptors of our creation.

metadata.name: Recon
metadata.description: Even the smallest blade can be deadly if you know where and how to strike.

metadata.name: Shady Merchant
metadata.description: No returns, no questions, no demonstrations. You break it, you buy it, if you survive.

metadata.name: DS-1 Prototype Frigate
metadata.description: “Commander, it just came up on the star chart, it must have slipped in from an undesignated jump point - it looks like its an Echelon ship but it's not responding.”

metadata.name: The Staff of Shoshanna
metadata.description: I heard that what she can do goes beyond healing. She not only mends broken bones and knits flesh, but she can give you power you never even knew you had.

metadata.name: Unfair Advantage
metadata.description: Taking on an Augencore warrior means taking on the genius of the whole ship.

metadata.name: Ruthless Sergeant
metadata.description: Courage falters. She does not.

metadata.name: Foundry Technician
metadata.description: The foundry-ships of the Augencore never cease their productions, the great furnaces at their core powering ship & industry alike.

metadata.name: Claymore Artillery Gun
metadata.description: The AX-0161 is a cornerstone in the Marcolian Assault Doctrine, rapidly redeploying & crushing fortifications that stand in it’s way.

metadata.name: Repurposed Hardware
metadata.description: Those first years on Mars would have been the death of us, but our ingenuity and resourcefulness kept us alive. Now it will be our enemies' downfall.

metadata.name: Malachite Shield
metadata.description: “We protect our planet, and in return, the very Earth itself rises to protect us.” - Soliea, Disciple of Gaffar

metadata.name: Revitalizing Growth
metadata.description: The breath of life flows through the Earthen, giving them strength to stand once again and defend their home.

metadata.name: Dark Allure
metadata.description: Power tends to corrupt, and absolute power corrupts absolutely.

metadata.name: Rug Poll
metadata.description: Ah, rug pollen. Grass near the source turns to a soft, plush velvet. Feels great between the toes, but get too comfortable and you’ll be too dizzy to tell the difference between your lover and a big ol’ blacktusk. Nasty little trick.

metadata.name: Chem-Crazed Bruiser [PL]
metadata.description: A veritable cocktail of combat enhancing substances, straight into the bloodstream. Useful in tight situations, not so much in diplomacy.

metadata.name: Erasure [PL]
metadata.description: A corpse can become a martyr. So we shall turn you to nothing.

metadata.name: The Flat Circle [PL]
metadata.description: In time, you will learn the meaning of eternity.

metadata.name: Hired Gun [PL]
metadata.description: Another of the Black Market’s specialties, you’ll find few questions are asked as long as your payment is on time.

metadata.name: Resourceful Smith [PL]
metadata.description: One man’s trash is another man’s mechanical killing machine.

metadata.name: Unstable Drone [SE]
metadata.description: Many an enemy of Mars has managed to take down such a machine, only to learn of the immediately fatal consequences.

metadata.name: Pirate Junker [SE]
metadata.description: “You paid money for this, sir? On purpose?” - Chloe, Renegade Pilot

metadata.name: Improvised Tactics [SE]
metadata.description: Marcolians possess a rather lethal form of ingenuity, and apply it liberally.

metadata.name: Kill Switch [SE]
metadata.description: Desperately outnumbered and beset upon from all sides, the valiant pilot had one last trick up their sleeve.

metadata.name: Honored Steward [SE]
metadata.description: The elite of the elite, woe unto anyone who finds themselves the prey of such a being.

metadata.name: Second Chance [SE]
metadata.description: Everyone deserves one.

metadata.name: Beacon of Gnaeus [SE]
metadata.description: The inspiring tales of Gnaeus Valerus Alpha’s valiant deeds spread far and wide. The mere mention of his name sowing fear in the enemies of the Kathari, and inspiring great feats of strength from his army.

metadata.name: Scrapheap Salvager [SE]
metadata.description: It’s not a glamorous job, but it serves a vital purpose ensuring little goes to waste.

metadata.name: Desperate Measures [SE]
metadata.description: Desperate times have always called for these.

metadata.name: Wisened Elder [SE]
metadata.description: Not all of us are here to fight, but we can all find a way to help

metadata.name: Hired Gun [SE]
metadata.description: Another of the Black Market’s specialties, you’ll find few questions are asked as long as your payment is on time.

metadata.name: Bionic Tweaker [SE]
metadata.description: 50% off of Ballistic Implants today! If you survive it malfunctioning, money back guarantee!

metadata.name: Resourceful Smith [SE]
metadata.description: One man’s trash is another man’s mechanical killing machine.

metadata.name: Technophobic Warrior [SE]
metadata.description: His ancestors hated people looking at their phones all the time.

metadata.name: Valerusi Striker [SE]
metadata.description: Many Kathari give a wide berth to the wild nature of the Strikers. Are they deadly? Most certainly. Effective? Sometimes.

metadata.name: Rainsoaked Mourner [SE]
metadata.description: On this day, we remember our brothers and sisters returned to the Earth.

metadata.name: Ceremonial Rites [SE]
metadata.description: Tradition is important. In dire times, it is even more vital to protect our ways.

metadata.name: The Flat Circle [SE]
metadata.description: In time, you will learn the meaning of eternity.

metadata.name: Engine Whisperer [SE]
metadata.description: The engines of the New Dawn barely resemble those the ship launched with centuries ago. Legends say the New Dawn can appear at almost any place in the system instantaneously, though few escape to tell the tale.

metadata.name: Vengeful Ally [SE]
metadata.description: Love is not the most powerful force in the world. Spite is.

metadata.name: Echelon Heavy [SE]
metadata.description: “Ah, I see you’ve met my business associate, Mr. Knuckles. Don’t worry about him, he will be a silent partner unless there’s any reason for him to become involved…”

metadata.name: Inspiring Teacher [SE]
metadata.description: She inspired those she taught. They were not going to let her death go unavenged.

metadata.name: Fire Support Base [SE]
metadata.description: Marcolians fiercely defend the territory they have gained, unwilling to give even an inch.

metadata.name: Valerusi Cohorts [SE]
metadata.description: The Cohorts of Gnaeus Valerus Alpha are a force to be reckoned with on the battlefield. Lacking any fear of death, they are an unrelenting wave of grey.

metadata.name: Hardlinked Pilot [SE]
metadata.description: Trained & bionically enhanced to be up to the task, these are the men & women who pilot the Augencore’s most devastating machines.

metadata.name: Chem-Crazed Bruiser [SE]
metadata.description: A veritable cocktail of combat enhancing substances, straight into the bloodstream. Useful in tight situations, not so much in diplomacy.

metadata.name: Security Officer [SE]
metadata.description: Trained to repel boarders & protect the secrets aboard their vessels at all costs, Augencore Security are not to be taken lightly.

metadata.name: Black Market Smuggler [SE]
metadata.description: Anything, anywhere. The Black Market is hard to beat for convenience.

metadata.name: TE4 Interceptor [SE]
metadata.description: Ships come in many shapes & sizes. Interceptor-class vessels are designed as hunter-killers, far outmaneuvering larger craft.

metadata.name: Heavy Weapons Team [SE]
metadata.description: Trained to work in perfect unison, the crewmen of the Marcolian Artillery Corps are the finest, and most lethal, gunners in the system.

metadata.name: The Void Unleashed
metadata.description: An eternity of waiting, unleashed in a single moment.

metadata.name: Signal Jammer
metadata.description: A favorite of Lemieux, these devices shut down enemy communication channels, which in turn allows his commandos to thrive in the confusion.

metadata.name: Shepherd of the Fallen
metadata.description: The Great One gave us life. It is only right that in time we give it back.

metadata.name: Shoshanna's Standard
metadata.description: Whenever they saw her flag making its way through the ranks they instinctively surged forward. They knew there was almost no injury she could not mend.

metadata.name: Anti-Organic Pulse
metadata.description: Most Augencore are loath to employ such devastating measures. For Arak, everything is a means to an end.

metadata.name: Orbital Patrol
metadata.description: Fury from the clouds, cast down in the blink of an eye.

metadata.name: Mortal Echo
metadata.description: We do not corrupt. We simply act upon what is inside.

metadata.name: Mournful Delta
metadata.description: Julius Delta looked down into eyes identical to his own, kissed his hand and bid himself farewell.

metadata.description: “If there's one thing the history of evolution has taught us, it's that life will not be contained. Life breaks free, it expands to new territories, and crashes through barriers painfully, maybe even dangerously”

metadata.name: Gallian Recombinant
metadata.description: “Maritus may be one of a kind, but if she is the future of the Children of Europa. We must remake ourselves in her image just as we are made in Galli’s.” - Fourth Palm of Galli

metadata.name: A.E.G.I.S. Generator
metadata.description: Augmented Energy Guard Individual System, the A.E.G.I.S. One of the Augencore’s most vital inventions for survival in a hostile world.

metadata.description: “The blood of Drusius Alpha flows through us all, his teachings burned into our memories. Embrace the power he has bestowed upon us!” - Vania Beta, Drusian Exhorator

metadata.description: “Of course, a Warden is accurate. But I’d trust one Marcolian Sniper over ten drones any day.” - Catherine Lapointe, Marcolian General

metadata.name: Iron Corps Rifleman
metadata.description: Mars expects that every man and woman will do their duty. Many of those look to the Iron Corps for inspiration.

metadata.name: EMP Shockwave [SE]
metadata.description: Winning a battle is significantly easier once your opponent can’t fight back.

metadata.name: Kamuy Protector [SE]
metadata.description: There is an ancient Earthen saying about these warriors. Roughly translated it comes out as “Don’t poke the Kamuy”

metadata.name: Squad Traitor [SE]
metadata.description: For those unwilling to believe in karma, many ways to get ahead can be found.

metadata.name: Aetian Subjugate [SE]
metadata.description: As our numbers swell, so too will our strength.

metadata.name: Innovative Apprentice [SE]
metadata.description: Ever learning, ever adapting. The future generations of the Augencore know they will be the ones to lead the way.

metadata.name: Repurposed Arms [SE]
metadata.description: Their ancestors wielded Pitchfork & Scythe to war. Now, the Augencore march onwards with a similar resourcefulness.

metadata.name: Rhetorician [SE]
metadata.description: Even now they take from us. We can no longer sit back and do nothing!

metadata.name: Life Well [SE]
metadata.description: Not all that awaits explorers of deep space is horrifying. Much of what is waiting to be discovered is, in human terms, quite miraculous. Tonight we bathe in the cosmos itself.

metadata.name: Infused Shaman [SE]
metadata.description: So skilled in the ways healing, the shaman can bring people back from the brink of death. But the cost… the earth demands balance.

metadata.name: Virulent Spores [SE]
metadata.description: Deadly to the touch, let alone if inhaled. The Earthen learn to use all their resources in defense of their land.

metadata.name: Valerusi Standard Bearer [SE]
metadata.description: “My friends, it is a fine day to die.” - Aramus Beta, Standard Bearer for the 8th Valerusi Cohort

metadata.name: Unseen Commando [SE]
metadata.description: Hand selected by legendary commando Lemieux, few rival the skills of Mars' finest.

metadata.name: Universal Soldier [SE]
metadata.description: Know your enemy. Their movements, their plans, even their thoughts - these are your weapons. Arm yourself.

metadata.name: Formidable Presence [SE]
metadata.description: The Earthen are a peace loving kind. Meev’Tsar is the exception that proves the rule.

metadata.name: The Staff of Shoshanna [SE]
metadata.description: I heard that what she can do goes beyond healing. She not only mends broken bones and knits flesh, but she can give you power you never even knew you had.

metadata.name: Iron Corps Quartermaster [SE]
metadata.description: Every round accounted for, not a single laser cell out of place. The Iron Corps operates with no margin of error.

metadata.name: Power Instructor [SE]
metadata.description: He does not bestow gifts, but teaches others to recognise their own.

metadata.name: Shady Merchant [SE]
metadata.description: No returns, no questions, no demonstrations. You break it, you buy it, if you survive.

metadata.name: Premonition [SE]
metadata.description: A vision from the Earth, a portent of things to come.

metadata.name: Pyrrhic Victory [SE]
metadata.description: When we look back on this day, I hope we can say it was worth it.

metadata.name: Crack Shot [SE]
metadata.description: Boom, Headshot.

metadata.name: Backup Copy
metadata.description: Before any of you dream of rebellion, know that you are one of thousands. With a mere push of a button, you can and will be replaced.

metadata.name: Technophobic Warrior
metadata.description: His ancestors hated people looking at their phones all the time.

metadata.name: Improvised Projectile
metadata.description: “Aerodynamics be damned, we can make it work” - Augencore Ship’s Gunner

metadata.name: Beacon of Gnaeus
metadata.description: The inspiring tales of Gnaeus Valerus Alpha’s valiant deeds spread far and wide. The mere mention of his name sowing fear in the enemies of the Kathari, and inspiring great feats of strength from his army.

metadata.name: Rainsoaked Mourner
metadata.description: On this day, we remember our brothers and sisters returned to the Earth.

metadata.name: Pirate Junker
metadata.description: “You paid money for this, sir? On purpose?” - Chloe, Renegade Pilot

metadata.name: Supply and Demand
metadata.description: Times may change, but the art of bargaining is eternal.

metadata.name: Improvised Tactics
metadata.description: Marcolians possess a rather lethal form of ingenuity, and apply it liberally.

metadata.name: Antius's Forecast
metadata.description: Antius was amongst the best of us. Perhaps, with this opportunity, you shall be too.

metadata.name: Bionic Tweaker
metadata.description: 50% off of Ballistic Implants today! If you survive it malfunctioning, money back guarantee!

metadata.name: Echelon Heavy
metadata.description: “Ah, I see you’ve met my business associate, Mr. Knuckles. Don’t worry about him, he will be a silent partner unless there’s any reason for him to become involved…”

metadata.name: Mind Twister
metadata.description: The Shroud cloud the minds of their enemies, making it near impossible to tell friend from foe.

metadata.name: Engine Whisperer
metadata.description: The engines of the New Dawn barely resemble those the ship launched with centuries ago. Legends say the New Dawn can appear at almost any place in the system instantaneously, though few escape to tell the tale.

metadata.name: Scanner Array
metadata.description: Long before you see us, we will know you are coming.

metadata.name: Desperate Measures
metadata.description: Desperate times have always called for these.

metadata.name: Wisened Elder
metadata.description: Not all of us are here to fight, but we can all find a way to help

metadata.name: Chem-Crazed Bruiser
metadata.description: A veritable cocktail of combat enhancing substances, straight into the bloodstream. Useful in tight situations, not so much in diplomacy.

metadata.name: Archivist's Pride
metadata.description: Our sequences are retained and so too, we hope, our souls.

metadata.name: Hired Gun
metadata.description: Another of the Black Market’s specialties, you’ll find few questions are asked as long as your payment is on time.

metadata.name: Longbow Personnel Carrier
metadata.description: Named after an ancient weapon of war, the Longbow delivers it’s lethal payload straight to the heart of the enemy.

metadata.name: Resourceful Smith
metadata.description: One man’s trash is another man’s mechanical killing machine.

metadata.name: Student of Shoshanna
metadata.description: Many among the Earthen believe studying the lessons of the past holds the key to our future.

metadata.name: Sacred Destruction
metadata.description: To Bela, the Great One bestowed a mere echo of his vast ability to destroy & remake as he sees fit. Bela’s faith is matched by few, as she views her role as divine purpose, arriving to aid only those Shroud she deems worthy of witnessing a vessel of their Master.

metadata.name: Heavy Weapons Team
metadata.description: Trained to work in perfect unison, the crewmen of the Marcolian Artillery Corps are the finest, and most lethal, gunners in the system.

metadata.name: Valerusi Striker
metadata.description: Many Kathari give a wide berth to the wild nature of the Strikers. Are they deadly? Most certainly. Effective? Sometimes.

metadata.name: Change of Heart
metadata.description: Look around and see what we are fighting over. We feel it and we can control it, and you are now a part of it. Violence and anger are a stain upon this vista. Find your calm and lower your weapon. Be at peace.

metadata.name: Unstable Drone
metadata.description: Many an enemy of Mars has managed to take down such a machine, only to learn of the immediately fatal consequences.

metadata.name: The Flat Circle
metadata.description: In time, you will learn the meaning of eternity.

metadata.name: Collateral Damage
metadata.description: Try as we might, there will always be unwanted casualties of war. Ideally, more for them than for us.

metadata.name: Cunning Scipian
metadata.description: “Scipians, we were grown for this. Our bodies will fuel the engines of war.” - Scipius Magnus Alpha

metadata.name: Fanatical Crewman
metadata.description: Many aboard the New Dawn seek to appease their unseen masters in the hopes of gaining power akin to the champions of the Shroud. Few are deemed worthy.

metadata.name: Second Chance
metadata.description: Everyone deserves one.

metadata.name: Valerusi Cohorts
metadata.description: The Cohorts of Gnaeus Valerus Alpha are a force to be reckoned with on the battlefield. Lacking any fear of death, they are an unrelenting wave of grey.

metadata.name: Tome of Aetio
metadata.description: “When all seems lost, remember that we are Kathari. Each of us hold the knowledge of a thousand deaths. Loss is only another path to victory.” - Aetio, Exalted Hydrolist

metadata.name: Fire Support Base
metadata.description: Marcolians fiercely defend the territory they have gained, unwilling to give even an inch.

metadata.name: Dark Dealings
metadata.description: A deal with the devil? Oh no, this is something far greater.

metadata.name: Tome of Aetio
metadata.description: “When all seems lost, remember that we are Kathari. Each of us hold the knowledge of a thousand deaths. Loss is only another path to victory.” - Aetio, Exalted Hydrolist

metadata.name: Steward of the Garden
metadata.description: Some beat their swords into plowshares. She preferred a trowel.

metadata.name: Mantis Corsair
metadata.description: Swift & agile beyond belief, mercantile craft pray they do not fall victim to a Mantis.

metadata.name: Combat Veteran
metadata.description: In the ways of war are best learned on the job, and there is no greater teacher than pain

metadata.name: Unseen Allies
metadata.description: “You may think you have me cornered, Kathari dogs, but I assure you the numbers are on my side”

metadata.name: Beloved Donor
metadata.description: “The greatest honour is to bestow oneself unto others.” - Octavia Delta, 2nd Cohort Physic

metadata.name: Hardlinked Pilot
metadata.description: Trained & bionically enhanced to be up to the task, these are the men & women who pilot the Augencore’s most devastating machines.

metadata.name: Security Officer
metadata.description: Trained to repel boarders & protect the secrets aboard their vessels at all costs, Augencore Security are not to be taken lightly.

metadata.name: Ceremonial Rites
metadata.description: Tradition is important. In dire times, it is even more vital to protect our ways.

metadata.name: Grove Altruist
metadata.description: The Grove teaches us that life and death are one and the same, each one a path to the other.

metadata.name: Heroic Pilot
metadata.description: There are those among the Augencore who have piloted their mechs for decades. I suggest you listen to their lessons.

metadata.name: Reckless Scientist
metadata.description: “Oh dear” - Last Recorded words of Dr. Noonian, esteemed Biochemist.

metadata.name: Life Siphon
metadata.description: “The group of suspected Shroud we encountered bore no arms, and moved with no urgency. Yet, many of us were lost that day.” - Unknown Kathari Archaeologist

metadata.name: Hydrolist Chamber
metadata.description: “I will see you again, my friend. Maybe even later today.” - Jubia Maximus Delta

metadata.name: Alkaline Hydrolist
metadata.description: “Welcome to the Hydroleum. Don’t forget your nose plugs. The smell is atrocious, at least that’s what they tell me.” - Chrysus, Alkaline Hydrolist

metadata.name: Singularity Steward
metadata.description: Every member of the Stewards would gladly give their life to prevent anyone getting close to discovering the Singularity. Thankfully, that’s not a fight that many would be foolish enough to take.

metadata.name: Black Market Smuggler
metadata.description: Anything, anywhere. The Black Market is hard to beat for convenience.

metadata.name: Unstable Shield Generator
metadata.description: “Uhh, Captain? I’m not sure our Shield is meant to be making that hissing noise”

metadata.name: Shaymak Stone-Eyes
metadata.description: In war, everyone is important. It’s not just those who fight and defend that will help us win, but those who keep them fighting and defending that will see us victorious.

metadata.name: Hidden Vaults
metadata.description: The vast resources of the Echelon Cartel allows them to hold influence in the highest of courts.

metadata.name: Life Stream
metadata.description: The prophecy told them to follow the stream, for it would lead to life eternal.

metadata.name: TE4 Interceptor
metadata.description: Ships come in many shapes & sizes. Interceptor-class vessels are designed as hunter-killers, far outmaneuvering larger craft.

metadata.name: Scanner Array
metadata.description: Long before you see us, we will know you are coming.

metadata.name: Paradigm Shift
metadata.description: We are Earthen. We are those that remained and as a reward the Earth itself can protect us. You just need to ask.

metadata.name: Honored Steward
metadata.description: The elite of the elite, woe unto anyone who finds themselves the prey of such a being.

metadata.name: Scrapheap Salvager
metadata.description: It’s not a glamorous job, but it serves a vital purpose ensuring little goes to waste.

metadata.name: Mercenary Gunslinger
metadata.description: If you’ve got the money, I’ve got the aim.

metadata.name: Interrogation Tools
metadata.description: Keeping secrets simply isn’t an option once Marcolian Intelligence has a hold of you.

metadata.name: Collateral Damage
metadata.description: Try as we might, there will always be unwanted casualties of war. Ideally, more for them than for us.

metadata.name: Smuggled Supplies
metadata.description: It never hurts to be prepared, and sometimes, it pays dividends.

metadata.name: Second Chance
metadata.description: Everyone deserves one.

metadata.name: Inspiring Teacher
metadata.description: She inspired those she taught. They were not going to let her death go unavenged.

metadata.name: Stoic Sellsword
metadata.description: There are those who would laugh at bringing a sword to a gun fight. This guy doesn’t seem worried about it.

metadata.name: Vengeful Ally
metadata.description: Love is not the most powerful force in the world. Spite is.

metadata.name: Synchronicity
metadata.description: I can always feel my brothers and sisters. Their thoughts are mine. Their feelings are mine. Their intent is mine. We may be many, but we act as one.

metadata.name: Paradigm Shift
metadata.description: We are Earthen. We are those that remained and as a reward the Earth itself can protect us. You just need to ask.

metadata.name: Enduring Immunus
metadata.description: Feeling death’s slow and icy embrace, Vitus Delta makes a stand.

metadata.name: Formatician's Exalt
metadata.description: Each Hydroleum has an Exalt. They are the bridge by which the Kathari travel from death to rebirth.

metadata.name: Determined Assault
metadata.description: Every Marcolian soldier knows that the greatness of Mars was bought with blood.

metadata.name: Marcolian Bannerman
metadata.description: The Banner of Mars flies high amongst the Marcolian forces. The act of carrying it is a great honour, often awarded to those who have shown great courage in past conflicts, as it is to be guarded with their life.

metadata.name: Erasure
metadata.description: A corpse can become a martyr. So we shall turn you to nothing.

metadata.name: Automation Expert
metadata.description: Automation is a highly controversial subject among the Augencore. Many employ its clear benefits, but there are those who claim nothing can replace the human touch in operating their machines.

metadata.name: Cape of Char Mahal
metadata.description: “This? It belonged to my father. When I was young, he used to tell me defense can win almost any fight, and when it can’t, at least I have my cape.” - Nehemiah

metadata.name: Kill Switch
metadata.description: Desperately outnumbered and beset upon from all sides, the valiant pilot had one last trick up their sleeve.

metadata.name: Artifact Appraiser
metadata.description: Cross-cultural expertise in artifacts of interest is a skill in high demand. Just make sure to hire good security.

metadata.name: Cutting Edge
metadata.description: For times when the simplest solution suffices.

metadata.name: Change of Heart
metadata.description: Look around and see what we are fighting over. We feel it and we can control it, and you are now a part of it. Violence and anger are a stain upon this vista. Find your calm and lower your weapon. Be at peace.
